#: src/0168-mod.md:47
msgid ""
"We introduce a way (the only way) to have paths in use items which do not "
"correspond with paths which can be used in the program. For example, with "
"`use foo::bar::{mod, baz};` the programmer can use `foo::bar::baz` in their "
"program but not `foo::bar::mod` (instead `foo::bar` is imported)."
